Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) says three people tested positive for coronavirus on Saturday. NCDC said this in its latest coronavirus data published for March 5, 2022. Saturday’s figure was the lowest number of daily new COVID-19 cases in 2022 so far. A breakdown of new cases showed that the states that reported the infections were Katsina (2) and Kaduna (1). No death figure was recorded from COVID-19 complications, leaving the death toll at 3,142. Meanwhile, the daily count of recoveries increased slightly, with 11 patients discharged on Saturday, increasing the total to 249,171. Since the index case in February 2020, Nigeria has confirmed 254,640 coronavirus infections. 3 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Katsina-2Kaduna-1 254,640 confirmed 249,171 discharged 3,142 deaths #TakeResponsibility pic.twitter.com/vg12fvOsog — NCDC (@NCDCgov) March 6, 2022 